div.div: Why: We are passionate about empowering individuals to transform their lives through the power of coding. We believe that everyone should have access to high-quality, affordable coding education, regardless of their background or experience.

br.div: What: We provide a comprehensive range of online programming courses, from beginner-level Web Development to advanced CSE Fundamentals and Advanced Programming Courses. Our courses are designed to be engaging, effective, and tailored to the needs of today's learners.

How: We nurture our students in a personalized and supportive environment that fosters confidence and success. Our friendly and dedicated instructors are always available to guide and mentor our students, ensuring they receive the support they need to achieve their coding goals.

self.__next_f.push([1,"Before starting the course, with the guidance of my friend who is a Senior Software Engineer, I have learnt HTML and CSS in 20 days from youtube and other resources. Then my friend told me to join the course as I have no idea what to do! I joined. The main thing I would say, I was in a guideline from Programming Hero Course Schedule and for that I have learnt smoothly and on time. The push was the Assignments, and it helped me a lot. Honestly, till Assignment-11 I couldn't feel that the course is at the verge of its end. I tried to complete the modules on time but in later at the time of Assignment-10, 11 it was hard for me and I couldn't completed on time and managed to complete the Assignments on time. I haven't watch any conceptual session lately but I could manage to complete the Assignments on time which proves, the modules are self sufficient for the course. Though it was told that at least 6-8 hours is needed everyday but except for the time of Assignment I barely managed 3/4 hours everyday but in my thinking it was every second even in my dream at night. So if anyone really wants to be a web developer, he/she needs to feel the thing, not just sit in front of laptop or desktop. Thinking and reading about everything patiently was the key for me during the journey. That why I could understand almost everything by only watching the modules. Thanks Programming Hero Team for their tremendous support also. "])

self.__next_f.push([1,"Alhamdulillah, my journey in the world of programming has been incredible, and it's all thanks to Programming Hero and my amazing mentors. One of the best motivators I've ever met is Jhankar Mahbub vai. His words always inspired me and kept me going, even when things got tough.
I also want to give a special thanks to my dear apu, Sumaiya Kabir. She was my Endgame mentor and an incredible help throughout my learning journey. She always cared for me and supported me with dedication, ensuring I understood everything and kept moving forward.
After completing a team project, I got the chance for job placement support. My job placement mentor, Sumiya Shajuti apu, was fantastic. She was always cool and supportive, guiding me on how to create a good resume, apply for jobs, and build connections. Her advice was invaluable, and thanks to her, I could navigate the job market effectively.
With these wonderful people's best support, I got hired not just once, but two times! Sometimes I can't believe it myself. The encouragement, guidance, and support I received made all the difference, and I am deeply grateful for it.
Thank you, Programming Hero, Jhankar Mahbub vai, Sumaiya Kabir apu, and Sumiya Shajuti apu. I am forever thankful that you all played a crucial role in my success."])

self.__next_f.push([1,"I started my journey through competitive programming in high school. However, by the time I finished high school, I started to lose interest in it. Just reading problem sets and finding solutions didn't seem intuitive to me. The first time I was introduced to web development was through a seminar on HTML and CSS. It was love at first sight. The idea of building something with my code that hundreds or thousands of users might find useful was particularly impressive to me.

After my H.S.C. exam, I joined the Programming Hero course. Despite the pressure of admission tests and other difficulties, I somehow finished the course on time with an almost perfect score. I was awarded the chance to join the Albatross group to start applying for jobs. I was placed in Abdullah Vai's server. However, due to ongoing exams and other external factors, I couldn't focus on applying for jobs and, as a result, got kicked out of the server. I was disappointed but didn't let that keep me from learning new technologies. I knew that my current knowledge wasn't going to be enough to land a job. So, I started experimenting with technologies like Next.js, TypeScript, and SQL databases that weren't taught in the course.

As I was on this journey of teaching myself, I got another chance with Project Sunshine. This time, I knew that I shouldn't let this chance slip by. So, I gave it my all and, after a month-long workshop, I was back in the same server with the same mentor. Maybe it was destiny. I worked tirelessly with Abdullah Vai and finally was able to land a job. Even though it wasn't through the recommendation channel or one of the jobs I applied to on my own, I am still grateful for the opportunity. Working with Abdullah Vai taught me a lot about how the industry works and how I should always strive to achieve the best version of myself."])

self.__next_f.push([1,"You can't finish talking about your course, brother. This is a wonderful course. By doing this course, I have only been able to learn web development, but not. I have learned how to do time management. Support sessions, deadlines for your assignments, course outlines are awesome. Moderates, admin brothers have suffered a lot. Every time I posted a help, I got a reply from the comments of the moderator / admin brothers. Many times I dropped out of the course due to family issues, exams, etc. It was really awesome when Jhangkar's brother inspired me to come back to the course with a zoom session. When I get frustrated again and again, I remember one of the words of Jhangkar Bhai: Life will have problems, obstacles will come, you have to deal with them. Many topics in the course will be a little shaky. If it weren't for the shock, everyone in the world would be a web developer. The problem actually has its solution. You have to find the solution. These words have inspired me a lot.\nIt's really awesome to find out by call, email."])
